Package edu.ncsu.csc216.wolf_scheduler.scheduler

Class WolfScheduler

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.ncsu.csc216.wolf_scheduler.scheduler.WolfScheduler
  • public class WolfScheduler
extends java.lang.Object
    WolfScheduler Class used for scheduling courses, adding events to schedule, getting courses from catalog, exporting schedules, removing courses from schedule, setting the schedule title, getting the schedule title, presenting activities in short or full descriptions, and adding events to schedule.
    Author:
    msabrams

      • addCourseToSchedule

        public boolean addCourseToSchedule​(java.lang.String name,
                                   java.lang.String section)
        Adds a course to the schedule from catalog
        Parameters:
        name - is the name of the course to add
        section - is the section of the course to add
        Returns:
        true if the course exists and is added to schedule or false if the course is not in schedule and can not be added.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if a user is already registered to a course they try to add or if there is a time conflict with the course to add and an activity in schedule.

      • removeActivityFromSchedule

        public boolean removeActivityFromSchedule​(int idx)
        Removes activity from schedule
        Parameters:
        idx - is the index of the activity you want to remove from schedule
        Returns:
        true if course was able/was removed from schedule and false if course was not able to be removed from schedule.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException - if the index parameter is out of bounds for the schedule ArrayList.

      • addEventToSchedule

        public void addEventToSchedule​(java.lang.String eventTitle,
                               java.lang.String eventMeetingDays,
                               int eventStartTime,
                               int eventEndTime,
                               java.lang.String eventDetails)
        Adds an event to the schedule
        Parameters:
        eventTitle - is the title of the event
        eventMeetingDays - is the meeting days of the event
        eventStartTime - is the start time of the event
        eventEndTime - is the end time of the event
        eventDetails - are the details of the event
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the event to add is already in the schedule or if there is a time conflict with the event to add with any activity already in schedule.
